<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1436,759,1404]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,308,1301,1327]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Remark.</emphasis>
Because of only a single described female of this species, it is difficult to compare it with other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1805" box="[278,373,1340,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[278,373,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Pholcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[413,488,1340,1366]" name="China" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">China</collectingCountry>
. However, the epigynum in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[981,1089,1340,1366]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="56.[151,256,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[169,1420,584,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-219@56.[149,1434,494,1942]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 28. Pholcus mengla Song &amp; Zhu, 1999 (illustrations modified from Song et al. 1999). A. female prosoma, dorsal view. B. female opisthosoma, lateral view. C. epigynum, ventral view. D. same, dorsal view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (A, B), 0.5mm (C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5362402/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28D</figureCitation>
) has some special characters and the carapace a special pattern (
<figureCitation box="[559,670,1378,1404]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="56.[151,256,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[169,1420,584,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-219@56.[149,1434,494,1942]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 28. Pholcus mengla Song &amp; Zhu, 1999 (illustrations modified from Song et al. 1999). A. female prosoma, dorsal view. B. female opisthosoma, lateral view. C. epigynum, ventral view. D. same, dorsal view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (A, B), 0.5mm (C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5362402/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
